Mixing spicy hot sauce with sweet honey makes the perfect glaze for these Quick Hot Honey Chicken Tacos. Ready in less than 25 minutes, you'll also toss potatoes with a quick Cajun spiced butter.

== Potatoes ==

If you don't have a microwave, heat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7 for the tortillas. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Halve the @salad potatoes{350%g} (no need to peel). Halve any larger potatoes again.

Pour the boiled water into a #medium saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} and bring back to the boil on high heat.

Add the potatoes to the water, lower the heat to medium and cook until tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

== Dressing ==

Meanwhile, trim the @baby gem lettuce{1}, halve lengthways, then thinly slice.

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the @cider vinegar{15%ml}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp}(for the dressing). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Set your dressing aside.

== Chicken ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{240%g} to the pan. Sprinkle over half the @cajun spice mix{1%sachet} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir-fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Cajun Potatoes ==

When the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and allow to steam for a few mins.

Return the potato pan to medium heat and melt half the @butter{30%g}.

Add the remaining Cajun spice mix and a pinch of @sugar{}. Cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add the potatoes back to the pan and toss to coat in the Cajun butter. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Remove from the heat and cover to keep warm.

== Tacos ==

Once cooked, add the @hot sauce{30%g}, @honey{15%g} and remaining butter to the chicken. TIP: If your honey has hardened, put the sachet in a bowl of hot water for ~{1%minute} to loosen.

Allow to melt and stir to combine, ~{1%minute}. Toss to coat the chicken, then remove from the heat.

Pile the @plain taco tortillas{4} (2 per person) onto a #plate{}. Heat them through in the #microwave{}, 850W: ~{50%seconds} / 750W: ~{1%minute}, until warm and soft.

If you're using the oven, pop them into the oven to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

== Assembly ==

When everything's ready, add the shredded baby gem to the dressing bowl and toss to coat.

Share the tortillas between your plates. Spread over the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}.

Top with the baby gem salad and chicken. Drizzle over any remaining sauce from the pan. Sprinkle over the cheese.

Serve the buttery Cajun potatoes alongside.

Enjoy!